# Stripe Configuration
# Get your API keys from: https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys

# ============================================================================
# PRODUCTION KEYS (Use these for live transactions)
# ============================================================================
# Secret key (server-side) - starts with sk_live_
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_51...YOUR_LIVE_SECRET_KEY

# Publishable key (client-side) - starts with pk_live_
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_51...YOUR_LIVE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY

# Webhook signing secret (from webhook endpoint configuration)
# Get from: https://dashboard.stripe.com/webhooks
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...YOUR_WEBHOOK_SECRET

# ============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT/TEST KEYS (Use these for testing only - comment out in production)
# ============================================================================
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_51...YOUR_TEST_SECRET_KEY
# STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_51...YOUR_TEST_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...YOUR_TEST_WEBHOOK_SECRET

# ============================================================================
# Important Notes:
# ============================================================================
# - Production keys start with: sk_live_ and pk_live_
# - Test keys start with: sk_test_ and pk_test_
# - NEVER use test keys (sk_test_) in production environments
# - Never commit actual keys to version control
# - Webhook secret is required for webhook signature verification
# - Toggle between test/live mode in Stripe Dashboard to get respective keys
# - The system will log a WARNING if test keys are detected in production
# ============================================================================
